𝐀𝐖𝐒 𝐕𝐏𝐂

𝐕𝐢𝐫𝐭𝐮𝐚𝐥 𝐏𝐫𝐢𝐯𝐚𝐭𝐞 𝐂𝐥𝐨𝐮𝐝 (𝐕𝐏𝐂)
A VPC is a private, isolated section of the cloud where you can define and control your networking environment. Within a VPC you can launch and manage cloud resources.

𝑪𝒓𝒆𝒂𝒕𝒊𝒏𝒈 𝑽𝑷𝑪

Go to the AWS Management Console.
Navigate to the VPC dashboard.
Click on "Create VPC" and specify the VPC details such as CIDR block. 

𝐒𝐮𝐛𝐧𝐞𝐭
A subnet (subnetwork) is a segment of your VPC that divides the larger VPC network into smaller, more manageable sections. Each subnet is assigned a range of IP addresses and can either be public (accessible from the internet) or private (isolated from the internet).

𝑪𝒓𝒆𝒂𝒕𝒊𝒏𝒈 𝑺𝒖𝒃𝒏𝒆𝒕𝒔
Navigate to the VPC dashboard.
Click on "Subnets" and then "Create Subnet".
Specify the subnet details including CIDR block and Availability Zone (AZ).

𝐈𝐧𝐭𝐞𝐫𝐧𝐞𝐭 𝐆𝐚𝐭𝐞𝐰𝐚𝐲(𝐈𝐆𝐖)
Allows communication between instances in your VPC and the internet.

𝑻𝒐 𝒄𝒓𝒆𝒂𝒕𝒆 𝒂𝒏 𝑰𝒏𝒕𝒆𝒓𝒏𝒆𝒕 𝑮𝒂𝒕𝒆𝒘𝒂𝒚:
Navigate to the VPC dashboard.
Click on "Internet Gateways" and then "Create Internet Gateway".
Attach the Internet Gateway to your VPC.

𝐑𝐨𝐮𝐭𝐢𝐧𝐠 𝐓𝐚𝐛𝐥𝐞𝐬:
Routing tables are essential for directing network traffic within your VPC. Routes can be set up to handle internal traffic between subnets or to other network services.

𝑻𝒐 𝒄𝒓𝒆𝒂𝒕𝒆 𝒂 𝒓𝒐𝒖𝒕𝒊𝒏𝒈 𝒕𝒂𝒃𝒍𝒆:
Navigate to the VPC dashboard.
Click on "Route Tables" and then "Create Route Table".
Define the routing rules, ensuring that traffic flows efficiently and securely to its intended destination. 
